#mergePDF: This script merges multiple PDF files into a single PDF document. It takes a list of input PDF files, combines them in the specified order and saves the result as one merged PDF file.

# Environment Setup Guide

# 1. Create a virtual environment
# python -m venv venv

# 2. Activate the virtual environment
# .\venv\Scripts\Activate

# 3. Install require library
# python -m pip install -r requirements.txt : use this command if you use the window power shell
# python -m pip install -r requirements.txt : use this command if you use the IDE terminal like PyCharm or VS code


# 4. Start the script: python main.py